{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"20915","heading":"Duration of registration requirement","label":"20915 Duration of registration requirement","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20915","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/stII/ch209/schI/ptA","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs20915","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","References in TextThis subchapter, referred to in subsec. (b)(2)(B), was in the original “this title”, meaning title I of , , , known as the Sex Offender Registration and Notification Act. For complete classification of title I to the Code, see Short Title of 2006 Act note set out under and Tables.Pub. L. 109–248120 Stat. 590section 10101 of this titleJuly 27, 2006","CodificationSection was formerly classified to , The Public Health and Welfare, prior to editorial reclassification and renumbering as this section.section 16915 of Title 42"],"amendments":["References in TextThis subchapter, referred to in subsec. (b)(2)(B), was in the original “this title”, meaning title I of , , , known as the Sex Offender Registration and Notification Act. For complete classification of title I to the Code, see Short Title of 2006 Act note set out under and Tables.Pub. L. 109–248120 Stat. 590section 10101 of this titleJuly 27, 2006"],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":"Full registration period","label":"a Full registration period","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20915/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20915","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs20915%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20915/a/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20915/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs20915%2Fa%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"15 years, if the offender is a tier I sex offender;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20915/a/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20915/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs20915%2Fa%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"25 years, if the offender is a tier II sex offender; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20915/a/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20915/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs20915%2Fa%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the life of the offender, if the offender is a tier III sex offender.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":"Reduced period for clean record","label":"b Reduced period for clean record","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20915/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20915","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs20915%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"Clean record","label":"1 Clean record","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20915/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20915/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs20915%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20915/b/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20915/b/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs20915%2Fb%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"not being convicted of any offense for which imprisonment for more than 1 year may be imposed;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20915/b/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20915/b/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs20915%2Fb%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"not being convicted of any sex offense;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20915/b/1/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20915/b/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs20915%2Fb%2F1%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"successfully completing any periods of supervised release, probation, and parole; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"D","heading":null,"label":"D","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20915/b/1/D","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20915/b/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs20915%2Fb%2F1%2FD","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"successfully completing of an appropriate sex offender treatment program certified by a jurisdiction or by the Attorney General.1So in original. The word “of” probably should not appear.1","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Period","label":"2 Period","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20915/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20915/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs20915%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20915/b/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20915/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs20915%2Fb%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a tier I sex offender, the period during which the clean record shall be maintained is 10 years; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20915/b/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20915/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs20915%2Fb%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a tier III sex offender adjudicated delinquent for the offense which required registration in a sex registry under this subchapter, the period during which the clean record shall be maintained is 25 years.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":"Reduction","label":"3 Reduction","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20915/b/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20915/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs20915%2Fb%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20915/b/3/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20915/b/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs20915%2Fb%2F3%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a tier I sex offender, the reduction is 5 years;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20915/b/3/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20915/b/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs20915%2Fb%2F3%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a tier III sex offender adjudicated delinquent, the reduction is from life to that period for which the clean record under paragraph (2) is maintained.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}]}
